Comparison methods
puts 1 > 2 # <= false
puts 1 < 2 # <= true

Strings compared by lexicographical ordering. Capital letters before lower case.
puts 'cat' < 'dog' # <= true
puts 'cat' > 'dog' # <= false
puts 'cat' < 'Dog' # <= false

puts 2 < 10 # <= true
puts '2' < '10' # <= false, looks at first character of string

== equal to
!= not equal to

Looping
input = ''
while input != 'bye'
  puts input
  input = gets.chomp
end
# loops by repeating answer given by user until 'bye' is entered

|| or
&& and

i_am_chris = true
i_am_purple = false
i_like_beer = true
i_eat_rocks = false

puts i_am_chris && i_like_beer <= true
puts i_like_beer && i_eat_rocks <= false
puts i_am_purple && i_like_beer <= false
puts i_am_purple && i_eat_rocks <= false
puts i_am_chris || i_like_beer <= true
puts i_like_beer || i_eat_rocks <= true
puts i_am_purple || i_like_beer <= true
puts i_am_purple || i_eat_rocks <= false
puts !i_am_purple <= true
puts !i_am_chris <= false
